{"action": "input", "code": "def get_start_position(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns the position of the first teal pixel (color code 8).\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                return (i, j)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    start = get_start_position(input_grid)\n    dir = get_teal_path_direction(start, input_grid)\n    out = extend_path(start, dir, input_grid)\n    out = reflect_and_extend_path(input_grid)\ndef extend_path(start: Tuple[int, int], direction: Tuple[int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting position of the first teal pixel, the direction of the teal path, and the input grid, \n    extends the path until it meets a red pixel (color code 2) using green pixels (color code 3).\n    \n    Args:\n    start: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    direction: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the direction of the teal path.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with the extended path.\n    \"\"\"\n    current_pos = start\n    while input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] != red:\n        input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] = green\n        current_pos = (current_pos[0] + direction[0], current_pos[1] + direction[1])\n    return input_grid\ndef get_teal_path_direction(start: Tuple[int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting position of the first teal pixel and the input grid, returns the direction of the teal path.\n    \n    Args:\n    start: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the row and column indices of the direction of the teal path.\n    \"\"\"\n    if start[0] == 0:\n        return (1, 0)\n    elif start[0] == input_grid.shape[0] - 1:\n        return (-1, 0)\n    elif start[1] == 0:\n        return (0, 1)\n    elif start[1] == input_grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        return (0, -1)\n    elif input_grid[start[0] - 1][start[1]] == teal:\n        return (-1, 0)\n    elif input_grid[start[0] + 1][start[1]] == teal:\n        return (1, 0)\n    elif input_grid[start[0]][start[1] - 1] == teal:\n        return (0, -1)\n    elif input_grid[start[0]][start[1] + 1] == teal:\n        return (0, 1)\ndef reflect_and_extend_path(start: Tuple[int, int], direction: Tuple[int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting position of the first teal pixel, the direction of the teal path, and the input grid, \n    extends the path until it meets a red pixel (color code 2) using green pixels (color code 3).\n    If the path encounters a black pixel (color code 0), it reflects and extends the path using green pixels (color code 3).\n    \n    Args:\n    start: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    direction: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the direction of the teal path.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with the extended and reflected path.\n    \"\"\"\n    current_pos = start\n    while input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] != red:\n        input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] = green\n        next_pos = (current_pos[0] + direction[0], current_pos[1] + direction[1])\n        if input_grid[next_pos[0]][next_pos[1]] == black:\n            if direction[0] == 0:\n                direction = (-direction[1], 0)\n            else:\n                direction = (0, -direction[0])\n        current_pos = (current_pos[0] + direction[0], current_pos[1] + direction[1])\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  start = `get the start position of teal pixel`(input_grid)\n  dir = `get the direction of teal path`(start, input_grid)\n  out = `use green to extend the path until meet red`(start, dir, input_grid)\n  out = `reflect and extend the path at the black area using green`(input_grid)\n", "gpt_code": "def get_start_position(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns the position of the first teal pixel (color code 8).\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                return (i, j)\ndef extend_path(start: Tuple[int, int], direction: Tuple[int, int], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting position of the first teal pixel, the direction of the teal path, and the input grid, \n    extends the path until it meets a red pixel (color code 2) using green pixels (color code 3).\n    \n    Args:\n    start: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the first teal pixel.\n    direction: A tuple containing the row and column indices of the direction of the teal path.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with the extended path.\n    \"\"\"\n    current_pos = start\n    while input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] != red:\n        input_grid[current_pos[0]][current_pos[1]] = green\n        current_pos = (current_pos[0] + direction[0], current_pos[1] + direction[1])\n    return input_grid\ndef ge